The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Dwayne Bravo: My No.1 performance 
                                                   Dwayne Bravo: My No.1 performance 
                      
	Dwayne Bravo, the first to score a fifty (actually 66 not out) and take four wickets in a T20 International, spoke to the media in general and briefly to The Telegraph separately, on Friday night.               
	The following are excerpts         
	Being a key performer for the West Indies         
	My passion for the game keeps driving me... I got an opportunity at the top of the order (No.4) and made the most.         
	His MoM-award winning performance         
	(Smiles) My most satisfying in any form of limited overs cricket... In fact, my No.1 performance... Now, I need to build on this... Four wickets and an unbeaten fifty...         
	[The 25-year-old Bravos best in an ODI is also against India  three for 32 and 61 not out in Port of Spain three summers ago.]         
	Whether he prefers a particular batting position         
	No... Im flexible... I dont have to bat at this number or that... The captain showed confidence today and I responded.         
	Lastly, on the IPL experience with the Mumbai Indians         
	I gained a lot and got the opportunity to share the dressing room with some greats...           OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT IN LONDON                                                                                                                   
